    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1997 Acura NSX-T, finished in Grand Prix White. This example features the mid-mounted 3.2L C32B V6, utilizing VTEC variable valve timing and factory titanium connecting rods to facilitate an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a precise 6-speed manual transaxle and a torque-sensing limited-slip differential. The extruded aluminum monocoque chassis remains structurally perfect, riding on an independent double-wishbone suspension with forged aluminum control arms. All mechanical systems are in peak operational state: the timing belt and water pump service is current, valve clearances are dialed to factory specifications, and there is zero seepage from the VTEC solenoid gaskets or cam end plugs. This is a concours-ready specimen offering unparalleled analog feedback and a pristine underbody.",
